It's given twice a week with a dosage of 400 units per kilogram.

00:15:45.090 --> 00:15:55.090
If you combine the two principles that is increasing the preoperative hematocrit and decreasing the threshold for allogeneic blood transfusion,

00:15:55.090 --> 00:16:02.090
then you can allow an even larger blood loss to occur without the need for allogeneic blood transfusion.

00:16:02.090 --> 00:16:10.090
Now this allowable blood loss can be further reduced certainly by surgical techniques or by anesthesiological techniques.

00:16:10.090 --> 00:16:24.090
Thus even such complex procedures as spinal surgery and redo open heart surgery are routinely performed with an even wider safety zone, afforded by the third pillar of a transfusion alternative protocol.

00:16:25.090 --> 00:16:31.090
Either by minimizing the bleeding or by recovering shed blood.

00:16:31.090 --> 00:16:36.090
Let's consider several important intraoperative techniques.

00:16:36.090 --> 00:16:41.090
Patient positioning is a simple cost-effective technique to reduce bleeding.

00:16:41.090 --> 00:16:51.090
Local venous pressure changes depending on the field's position relative to the heart and lower pressure directly correlates with blood saved.

00:16:52.090 --> 00:16:55.090
It's important to position the patient properly due to an orthopedic surgery.

00:16:55.090 --> 00:17:00.090
In my experience, it makes a big difference in spinal surgery.

00:17:00.090 --> 00:17:05.089
With pressure on the abdomen and thus on the paravertebral veins, blood loss increases.

00:17:05.089 --> 00:17:11.089
With proper support, avoiding abdominal compression, blood loss decreases.

00:17:11.089 --> 00:17:18.089
Another option to decrease venous pressure in some surgeries is to use regional instead of general anesthesia.

00:17:18.089 --> 00:17:27.089
As shown here, prior to a cesarean section, a further technique is the maintenance of normal thermia, especially during long operations.

00:17:27.089 --> 00:17:36.089
So if a patient is cool or cold by one or two degrees temperature, you are seeing a loss in ability of platelets and coagulation factors to work.

00:17:36.089 --> 00:17:39.089
So it's essential that we keep the patient's normal thermic.

00:17:39.089 --> 00:17:42.089
Normal thermia is extremely important.

00:17:42.089 --> 00:17:48.089
Therefore, our operating theatre temperatures are 27 degrees in those major procedures.

00:17:48.089 --> 00:17:54.089
Which sometimes is hard for the surgeons, even for the anesthesiologists, but it's very good for the patient.

00:17:54.089 --> 00:18:00.089
More directly, the patient's body can be warmed with a thermal suit or blankets.

00:18:00.089 --> 00:18:06.460
There are even simple machines to warm fluids before infusion.

00:18:06.460 --> 00:18:09.460
Next, hemodolution.

00:18:09.460 --> 00:18:16.460
The principles of hemodolution in terms of reduction of blood loss are really quite simple.

00:18:16.460 --> 00:18:28.460
If blood is removed from the patient immediately prior to or immediately after induction of anesthesia and replaced with a cellular fluids,

00:18:28.460 --> 00:18:34.460
then when the patient bleeds interoperatively, the red cell loss is less.

00:18:34.460 --> 00:18:42.460
For every 100 ml of whole blood lost by the patient, in the case of a patient with a hematocard of 27%,

00:18:42.460 --> 00:18:54.460
they're going to lose 27 ml of RBCs rather than the 45 ml of RBCs they would have lost had we started the case at a hematocard of 45%.

00:18:54.460 --> 00:19:00.460
Additionally, the hemodolution procedure is acceptable to a number of Jehovah's Witnesses.

00:19:00.460 --> 00:19:14.900
Hemodolution is certainly cost-effective, but not only that, it is also beneficial for the patient as it improves blood rheology as has been shown by many studies.

00:19:14.900 --> 00:19:24.900
Another transfusion alternative technique for selected surgeries is induced hypotension to lower mean arterial pressure intraoperatively.

00:19:24.900 --> 00:19:32.900
Usually, a drug is used to decrease systemic vascular resistance. This typically prevents up to 50% of blood loss.

00:19:32.900 --> 00:19:43.900
Anesthesiologists urge caution when combining hypotension with hemodolution because hypotension can interfere with the normal redistribution of blood flow.

00:19:43.900 --> 00:19:50.900
A crucial factor that requires skill and patience is meticulous surgical hemostasis and technique.

