The basic technique for a surgeon to control bleeding is to ligate the vessels.

00:20:01.900 --> 00:20:05.900
That's true for all the vessels, let's say, down to one millimeter in diameter.

00:20:05.900 --> 00:20:13.900
If there's some bleeding persisting, there are calculation techniques, best of which is at the moment argon beam calculations.

00:20:13.900 --> 00:20:16.900
We use it routinely in liver transplantation.

00:20:17.900 --> 00:20:20.900
Hemostatic agents can also assist.

00:20:20.900 --> 00:20:31.900
There is two types of agents, general agents that could be administered intravenously, such as trannix amicacid or aprotinin.

00:20:31.900 --> 00:20:43.900
And the surgeons have also the possibility to use topical glues in order to better control the bleeding in the surgical field.

