00:21:01.900 --> 00:21:10.900
If intraoperative bleeding becomes heavy, a cell salvage machine, often kept on standby, is able to recover the shed blood.

00:21:11.900 --> 00:21:22.900
As the blood flows through the device, some machines simply filter out any debris, while other types include the additional step of washing the red cells as they circulate.

00:21:22.900 --> 00:21:29.900
